{
  "texts": [
    "Data2vec and the Supervised approach performed very comparatively, often interchanging second and third place in performance.",
    "Unfrozen Feature ExtractorFigure 7 compares the SSL techniques when the feature extractor is unfrozen.",
    "While we observe that the best results are generally obtained by pre-training the classifier in a supervised fashion (that is an unrealistic scenario), MAE was ranked 2nd in all cases except with results not far behind.The worst-performing results, in general, were models that were pre-trained with SimCLR.",
    "Data2vec often performed in the middle ground compared to other techniques, except when we used the iSPL model on the MotionSense dataset, where data2vec performed poorly between the 1 -10 samples per class range.",
    "Table 6 presents the number of FLOPs and parameters for the two architectures after the needed adaption for each pre-training technique."
